30  def from_local_objects_detected(self, local_objects_pc):
31  """
32  This function is called when a new point cloud is received from the local object detector.
33  @param local_objects_pc: The point cloud of the objects detected by the local object detector.
34  @type local_objects_pc: PointCloud2
35  @return: None
36  """
37 
38  if self.freeze_objects:
39  return
40 
41  local_points = point_cloud2.read_points_list(local_objects_pc)
42 
43  fields = [PointField('x', 0, PointField.FLOAT32, 1),
44  PointField('y', 4, PointField.FLOAT32, 1),
45  PointField('z', 8, PointField.FLOAT32, 1),
46  # PointField('rgb', 12, PointField.UINT32, 1),
47  #PointField('rgba', 12, PointField.UINT32, 1),
48  ]
49 
50  header = rospy.Header()
51  header.frame_id = "map"
52  header.stamp = local_objects_pc.header.stamp
53 
54  self.add_new_detected_points(local_points)
55  point_cloud = point_cloud2.create_cloud(

60  def add_new_detected_points(self, new_points):
61  """
62  add new points to the global map.
63  @param new_points: The points to add to the global map.
64  @type new_points: numpy array of points.
65  @return: None
66  """
67  rospy.loginfo_throttle(5, "prior points" +
68  str(len(self.global_objects)))
69  # print("<dist>")
70  for new_point in new_points:
71  if len(filter(lambda x: not(np.isnan(x)), new_point)) != 3: continue
72  if new_point[2] < 0.1:
73  continue
74  if self.get_close_point_indices(new_point, self.global_objects) > 0.40:
75  self.global_objects = np.vstack(
76  (self.global_objects, new_point))
77  # print("added points")
78  # print("</dist>")
79  rospy.loginfo_throttle(5, "new points" + str(len(new_points)))
80  rospy.loginfo_throttle(5, "posterior points" +
81  str(len(self.global_objects)))
82 
83  def get_close_point_indices(self, node, nodes):
84  """
85  This function returns the indices of the points in the nodes array that are close to the node.
86  @param node: The point to check for close points.
87  @type node: numpy array of points.
88  @param nodes: The array of points to check for close points.
89  @type nodes: numpy array of points.
90  @return: The indices of the points in the nodes array that are close to the node.
91  @rtype: numpy array of indices.
92  """
93  if len(nodes) == 0:
94  return np.inf
95  nodes = np.asfarray(nodes)
96  dist_2 = np.sqrt(np.sum((nodes - node)**2, axis=1))
97  # print(dist_2)
98  return dist_2[np.argmin(dist_2)]
